      "text": "Constantia was incorporated as a village in 1836 but abandoned that status in 1923.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantia_(CDP)%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The Trinity Church in Constantia was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1982.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantia_(CDP)%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Constantia’s name honors George Scriba, a German immigrant who bought half a million acres after the Revolution.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        22
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://constantiany.org/our-history.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Early settlers were drawn to Constantia by Oneida Lake’s abundant forests and easy lake transport.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://constantiany.org/our-history.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The Erie Canal and later the Ontario and Western railroad turned Constantia into a market garden and fresh fish hub.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://constantiany.org/our-history.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "The historic Constantia Center, once a schoolhouse, now serves as the town’s community hub.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
